Class ResourcePath

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.paths.Path<java.lang.String>
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.paths.StringPath
        • com.telenav.kivakit.core.resource.ResourcePath
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Countable, Sized, java.lang.Comparable<Path<java.lang.String>>, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FilePath
    public class ResourcePath
extends StringPath
    A path to a resource of any kind. By default the separator character for a resource is forward slash. But in the case of some file paths this may be overridden. For example, in FilePath.

    This class contains numerous methods which down-cast the return value of the superclass to make use easier for clients. Methods that are unique to this class mainly have to do with filenames and file paths:

    • asFile() - This resource path as a file
    • asFilePath() - This resource path as a file path
    • fileName() - The last component of this path as a FileName
    • normalized() - This path without characters invalid in a resource path
    • withExtension(Extension) - This path with the given extension

    Parsing

    • parseResourcePath(String) - The given string as a resource path
    • parseUnixResourcePath(String) - The given string as a slash-separated UNIX resource path

    Factories

    • resourcePath(StringPath) - The given string path as a resource path
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)

        Returns:
        The subpath of this path starting at given start index (inclusive) and extending to the end index (exclusive). If start and end are equal, the empty path is returned. If start and end are not equal and the path is absolute, the subpath will still be absolute with the same root. If the start and end indexes are invalid, null is returned.
